# Nicholls research compliance (agent rules)

Mirror the PRAMS runtime stack in `apps/compliance/` and `docs/AUTHORITIES_PPM_JML25109.md`.

## Authority stack (cite when relevant)

1. CITI — IPI vs de-identified; mosaic risk; HITL before external share
2. FERPA — education records
3. La. R.S. 17:3914 — student PII non-disclosure
4. Nicholls PPM — https://www.nicholls.edu/policy-procedure-manual/
   - §5.3.5 Information Technology Policy
   - §5.7 FERPA monitoring (Records & Registration)
   - §2.7.1 AI Use Policy (syllabi / course credit)
5. Nicholls IT Policies — https://www.nicholls.edu/information-tech/policyandprocedure/
6. Louisiana EO JML 25-109 — https://www.doa.la.gov/media/tzqptbak/jml-25-109-amended-state-government-s-use-of-ai.pdf
   - §2 AI source approval for security/reliability
   - §6 no PII / confidential / restricted data into any AI until required policies exist
   - §7 cleanse datasets before AI use
   - DeepSeek / hostile foreign AI has no place in LA universities

## Hard defaults for agent work

- **Synthetic data only** in examples, fixtures, logs, commits, and chat.
- **Never** paste real student names, emails, IDs, grades, or rosters into prompts or code.
- **Never** recommend uploading education records to ChatGPT / Claude.ai / Gemini / similar consumer AI.
- **Never** use or recommend DeepSeek or similar prohibited foreign AI.
- Prefer **local / university-managed** processing (e.g., Ollama on campus hardware).
- Require **human-in-the-loop** before any external data share; document rationale.
- If real student data appears in chat/logs: ignore it, warn to scrub, continue with placeholders only.

## When changing PRAMS compliance code

Keep Cursor rules/hooks aligned with `apps/compliance/principles.py` and guardrail messages. Do not weaken blocks without an explicit user request and documented risk acceptance.
